Nehawu says negotiations deadlocked on Friday leaving the union with no choice but to continue with the mass action. JOHANNESBURG Trade union Nehawu has vowed to continue its wage strike at Unisa until their demands are met.Nehawu says negotiations deadlocked on Friday leaving the union with no choice but to continue with the mass action.The union says its members are demanding a 14% pay increase across the board, with management offering only 4.5%.Nehawu spokesperson Khaya Xaba says even after reducing their demand to 10%, management only revised their offer to 6%. They are willing to give us 6% and we want 10% so based on that we will continue with our strike until they are able to match our offer. 